<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="185" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1612,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1899,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species is allied to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Liu, 2012" authorityName="Wang &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2012" box="[676,1303,1900,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Neocyrtopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax" subGenus="Neocyrtopsis">
<emphasis box="[676,1072,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Neocyrtopsis (Neocyrtopsis) fallax</emphasis>
Wang &amp; Liu, 
<number box="[1244,1303,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter in: male pronotum moderately shorter, metazona slightly raised; cerci curved, apices directed anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
